---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy | KONVOI',
  description: 'Privacy policy for KONVOI GmbH pursuant to GDPR and TDDDG.',
  robots: { index: true, follow: true },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>
      Protecting your personal data is important to us. This privacy policy informs you pursuant to
      Art. 13 GDPR and § 25 TDDDG (German Telecommunications Digital Services Data Protection Act)
      about how we collect, process, and protect your data.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Controller</h2>

    <p>
      KONVOI GmbH<br />
      Harburger Schlossstraße 6-12<br />
      21079 Hamburg<br />
      Germany<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:info@konvoi.eu">info@konvoi.eu</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Collection and Processing of Personal Data</h2>

    <p>
      We collect and process personal data only to the extent necessary for providing our website and
      services, or where you have given your explicit consent. The following sections explain which
      service providers and processing activities are involved.
    </p>

    <h2>Hosting and Content Delivery</h2>

    <p>
      This website is hosted by:<br />
      <strong>Netlify Inc.</strong><br />
      44 Montgomery Street Suite 300<br />
      San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Purpose:</strong> Providing the website and delivering static content via a Content
      Delivery Network (CDN).<br />
      <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in a reliable,
      secure, and performant website).<br />
      <strong>Data processed:</strong> Netlify processes access logs that may include IP addresses,
      browser information, and timestamps. These logs are used for security and diagnostic purposes.
    </p>

    <p>
      For more information, see Netlify's privacy policy:
      <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        https://www.netlify.com/privacy/
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>Forms and Contact Requests</h2>

    <p>
      When you use our contact or consultation forms, the data you enter is transmitted to us via
      <strong>Web3Forms</strong> (api.web3forms.com).
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Purpose:</strong> Transmitting contact and consultation requests to KONVOI GmbH.<br />
      <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a GDPR (consent given by actively submitting
      the form).<br />
      <strong>Data processed:</strong> Name, email address, form content.
    </p>

    <p>
      The transmitted data is used exclusively to respond to your request. Web3Forms forwards the data
      by email and does not store permanent copies. For more information:
      <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        https://web3forms.com/privacy
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>Bot Protection on Forms</h2>

    <p>
      Our forms are protected by <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong>, a service provided by:<br />
      Cloudflare Inc.<br />
      101 Townsend St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Purpose:</strong> Protection against automated requests (bots) and abuse of contact
      forms.<br />
      <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in the security of
      our website and services).<br />
      <strong>Cookie:</strong> Cloudflare Turnstile sets a technically necessary cookie
      (<code>cf_clearance</code>) required for bot protection. This cookie falls under the exemption
      for technically necessary cookies pursuant to § 25 para. 2 no. 2 TDDDG and does not require
      separate consent.
    </p>

    <p>
      For more information:
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics (Rybbit)</h2>

    <p>
      We use <strong>Rybbit</strong>, a privacy-friendly, self-hosted analytics tool to anonymously
      evaluate the use of our website.
    </p>

    <p>
      Rybbit uses <strong>no cookies</strong> and stores <strong>no personal data</strong>. Analysis
      is based on anonymised technical characteristics — no IP addresses are stored and no
      fingerprinting of personal data takes place.
    </p>

    <p>
      Since no data is stored on or read from end-user devices, consent under § 25 para. 1 TDDDG
      (German Telecommunications Digital Services Data Protection Act) is not required. Processing is
      based on § 25 para. 2 no. 2 TDDDG in conjunction with Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate
      interest in anonymous reach measurement to improve our website).
    </p>

    <p>
      Rybbit is self-hosted — <strong>no data is transmitted to third parties</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>Appointment Booking (Cal.eu)</h2>

    <p>
      Our website contains links to the external booking service <strong>Cal.eu</strong> (cal.eu).
      When you click these links, you leave our website and are redirected directly to Cal.eu.
      <strong>No Cal.eu data is embedded on our website</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For data processing on Cal.eu's website, only Cal.eu's own privacy policy applies. We have no
      influence over their data processing.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies and Consent Management</h2>

    <p>
      We use <strong>vanilla-cookieconsent v3</strong> to manage your cookie consents. This tool
      informs you on your first visit to our website about the use of cookies and allows you to grant
      or refuse consent.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Technically necessary cookies</strong> (e.g. Cloudflare Turnstile
        <code>cf_clearance</code>) are set without consent, as they are strictly required for the
        basic functions of the website (§ 25 para. 2 no. 2 TDDDG).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Optional cookies</strong> (e.g. Google Maps on the contact page) are only loaded
        after your explicit consent.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Your consent decision is stored in your browser (cookie <code>cc_cookie</code>,
      SameSite=Lax). You can withdraw or adjust your consent at any time via the
      <strong>"Cookie Settings"</strong> link in the footer of this website.
    </p>

    <h2>Social Media</h2>

    <p>
      We maintain a company profile on <strong>LinkedIn</strong> (LinkedIn Ireland Unlimited Company,
      Wilton Place, Dublin 2, Ireland). When you visit our LinkedIn page, LinkedIn processes your
      data in accordance with its own privacy policy:
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy
      </a>
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>No LinkedIn tracking pixels or plugins are embedded</strong> on our own website.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Rights (Data Subject Rights)</h2>

    <p>
      You have the following rights with regard to your personal data:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
      <li>Right to object to processing (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      To exercise your rights, please contact:
      <a href="mailto:info@konvoi.eu">info@konvoi.eu</a>
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority:</strong><br />
      You have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent data protection supervisory authority:
    </p>

    <p>
      Der Hamburgische Beauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit (HmbBfDI)<br />
      Ludwig-Erhard-Str. 22<br />
      20459 Hamburg, Germany<br />
      Email:
      <a href="mailto:mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de">mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
